# Documentation Freshness

When modifying files matched by this rule, check whether the corresponding knowledge-base documentation needs updating.

## Scope

This rule monitors two packages that have dedicated knowledge-base documentation maintained for Cursor agent context:

| Package | Why monitored |
|---|---|
| `packages/sdk/` | 5 knowledge rules document SDK internals: schemas, config, cache management, model constants, delegated inference |
| `packages/registry-server/` | 1 skill documents Autobase/HyperDB patterns, schema build pipeline, and implementation gotchas |

**Not monitored:** Individual addon packages (`transcription-whispercpp`, etc.). Their corresponding docs (`qvac-whispercpp-example.mdc`) describe external library APIs as static reference material — they drift when upstream libraries change, not when our source changes. Glob-based monitoring can't catch that; those docs are better maintained through periodic review.

